# KUKA WorkVisual

WorkVisual is KUKA's primary engineering tool. It owns:

- I/O configuration (Profinet / EtherNet-IP / EtherCAT topology, fieldbus mapping, safety I/O signals).
- Machine data (`$machine.dat`) — mastering, payloads, calibration.
- System configuration (`$config.dat`) — aliases, defaults.
- Option package installation (SafeOperation, mxAutomation, RSI, ConveyorTech, etc.).
- Long-text bundles for HMI.

## What Lives Where

| Artifact | Owner | Editable in Cursor? |
|----------|-------|---------------------|
| `$config.dat` — user aliases, shared decls | WorkVisual primary; source edit possible | Yes, with care; WV deploy overwrites |
| `$machine.dat` — calibration, mastering | WorkVisual | No — WV only |
| Robot programs (`.src`/`.dat`) | Teach pendant + WV + source control | Yes — primary Cursor surface |
| I/O mapping | WorkVisual | No — WV only |
| SafeOperation zone config | WorkVisual + SafeOperation Configurator | No |

## Interaction Rules

- Do not manually edit fieldbus topology; it is exported from WorkVisual.
- When adding a new signal alias, edit `$config.dat` **and** mirror the change in the WorkVisual project (document in the handoff).
- Source-control the WorkVisual project (`.wvs` / project folder). Commit both the WV project and the exported `$config.dat` when they change.

## Exports to Read

- `WVExport/` — if you export the WV project to inspect in source, place it here.
- `kuka_dataset/normalized/articles/ONE_*_WorkVisual_*.md` for usage patterns (once populated).

